{"id": "EUVD-2018-0571", "enisaUuid": "eeb88e7b-87d2-399a-80c6-e9a0ee167ade", "description": "Apache Mesos can be configured to require authentication to call the Executor HTTP API using JSON Web Token (JWT). In Apache Mesos versions pre-1.4.2, 1.5.0, 1.5.1, 1.6.0 the comparison of the generated HMAC value against the provided signature in the JWT implementation used is vulnerable to a timing attack because instead of a constant-time string comparison routine a standard `==` operator has been used. A malicious actor can therefore abuse the timing difference of when the JWT validation function returns to reveal the correct HMAC value.", "datePublished": "2018-09-21T13:00:00", "dateUpdated": "2024-09-16T16:58:25", "baseScore": 5.9, "baseScoreVersion": "3.0", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:N", "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2018-8023", "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-c8cc-p3j7-4c7f", "https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/9b9d3f6bd09f3ebd2284b82077033bdc71da550a1c4c010c2494acc3@%3Cdev.mesos.apache.org%3E", "https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r0dd7ff197b2e3bdd80a0326587ca3d0c22e10d1dba17c769d6da7d7a@%3Cuser.flink.apache.org%3E", "https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/9b9d3f6bd09f3ebd2284b82077033bdc71da550a1c4c010c2494acc3%40%3Cdev.mesos.apache.org%3E", "https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r0dd7ff197b2e3bdd80a0326587ca3d0c22e10d1dba17c769d6da7d7a%40%3Cuser.flink.apache.org%3E"], "aliases": ["CVE-2018-8023", "GHSA-c8cc-p3j7-4c7f"], "assigner": "apache", "epss": 0.8, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "60009488-ccad-3f63-9703-588013825b1b", "product": {"name": "Apache Mesos"}, "product_version": "versions prior to 1.4.2"}, {"id": "634ffe01-09b7-394e-9b27-9a433f318bd5", "product": {"name": "Apache Mesos"}, "product_version": "1.6.0"}, {"id": "98381406-a9c2-3bf8-aaf6-bc3cb0f91f53", "product": {"name": "Apache Mesos"}, "product_version": "1.5.0, 1.5.1"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "a5b42dbb-c73c-36eb-afd8-4bcf203ada4e", "vendo